2
00:03:15,172 --> 00:03:19,734
I guess with the idea that sometimes
things happen that we don't understand.

3
00:03:20,577 --> 00:03:23,137
Maybe we shouldn't try to.

4
00:03:24,681 --> 00:03:29,345
My dad had been assigned to inspect
the military southern sector of the EPA.

5
00:03:29,419 --> 00:03:34,254
My stepmother, my half-brother and I
spent two months on the road with him.

6
00:03:34,491 --> 00:03:39,292
It's hard being in a car with a 6-year-old
and the woman who replaced your mom.

7
00:03:41,131 --> 00:03:43,895
But nobody asked me what I wanted
to do that summer.

8
00:03:45,235 --> 00:03:47,726
I guess things do happen for a reason...

9
00:03:48,238 --> 00:03:50,832
...even if you don't like what that reason is.

10
00:04:18,635 --> 00:04:20,034
Come on.

11
00:04:24,141 --> 00:04:25,472
Fill it up.

12
00:04:26,443 --> 00:04:29,571
- You got a rest room?
- It ain't great, but we've got one.

13
00:04:29,646 --> 00:04:32,206
- Not the "big old fat" part.
- Which part?

14
00:04:32,382 --> 00:04:34,373
- Can I have a soda?
- No.

15
00:04:34,451 --> 00:04:36,749
- I see you're from Washington, D.C.
- That's right.

16
00:04:36,820 --> 00:04:38,287
Long way from home.

17
00:04:59,676 --> 00:05:01,667
You're bad. You're bad.

18
00:05:04,047 --> 00:05:05,309
You're scared.

19
00:05:05,415 --> 00:05:06,404
Good.

20
00:05:09,419 --> 00:05:10,909
They're out there.

21
00:05:12,055 --> 00:05:13,454
They're everywhere!

22
00:05:13,523 --> 00:05:15,354
They get you when you sleep.

23
00:05:15,892 --> 00:05:18,156
They get you when you sleep, you hear?

24
00:05:18,528 --> 00:05:20,826
Get out, or you'll be next!

25
00:05:22,499 --> 00:05:24,126
Dad! Dad!

26
00:05:25,268 --> 00:05:27,099
There's a psycho in there!

27
00:05:27,170 --> 00:05:29,161
- In the bathroom?
- He's got a knife!

28
00:05:31,942 --> 00:05:33,239
Sweetheart?

29
00:05:33,310 --> 00:05:36,370
Maybe you should let him go in first.
He's got a gun.

30
00:05:37,214 --> 00:05:39,774
Maybe you'd better come back here, honey.

31
00:05:45,589 --> 00:05:47,079
There's nothing here.

32
00:05:48,725 --> 00:05:50,454
There's no one in there.

33
00:05:52,028 --> 00:05:53,222
You okay?

34
00:05:53,363 --> 00:05:54,728
No one's there?

35
00:05:55,932 --> 00:05:57,695
Marti, are you okay?

36
00:05:59,870 --> 00:06:04,136
Are you all right? What did he want?
Maybe we should file a police report.

37
00:06:06,142 --> 00:06:08,303
"They get you when you sleep."

38
00:06:08,478 --> 00:06:10,912
I remember thinking he was crazy...

39
00:06:10,981 --> 00:06:14,815
...but I also remember thinking
we spend half our lives asleep.

40
00:06:19,956 --> 00:06:21,287
'Morning, sir.

41
00:06:21,625 --> 00:06:24,025
I'm Steve Malone. I'm with the EPA.

42
00:06:24,094 --> 00:06:26,062
