55
00:07:56,119 --> 00:07:57,381
Great.

56
00:08:00,023 --> 00:08:02,753
Andy, come on. Help me unload the car.

57
00:08:09,933 --> 00:08:13,369
Come on, I'm going to get there
before you do.

58
00:08:49,139 --> 00:08:50,800
Andy, honey, slow down.

59
00:08:50,874 --> 00:08:52,637
There are only two bedrooms.

60
00:08:52,809 --> 00:08:55,403
You've got to share with your brother then.

61
00:08:58,548 --> 00:09:01,210
Steve, can you give me a hand up here?

62
00:09:02,318 --> 00:09:03,910
Don't work too hard.

63
00:09:27,677 --> 00:09:31,238
If we'd known what was waiting for us,
we would've run.

64
00:09:32,415 --> 00:09:34,645
But, in the end, it had to happen.

65
00:09:35,885 --> 00:09:37,819
And so it began.

66
00:09:43,693 --> 00:09:46,253
- This is a restricted area, miss.
- What?

67
00:09:50,500 --> 00:09:53,333
You shouldn't be here
without security clearance.

68
00:10:00,210 --> 00:10:01,199
What's up?

69
00:10:02,779 --> 00:10:04,212
Get in the car.

70
00:10:28,071 --> 00:10:29,402
I'm Jenn.

71
00:10:29,572 --> 00:10:30,504
Marti.

72
00:10:30,573 --> 00:10:32,165
Thanks for picking me up.

73
00:10:32,242 --> 00:10:34,142
No problem. They're dicks.

74
00:10:34,310 --> 00:10:36,141
What was that all about?

75
00:10:36,312 --> 00:10:40,146
God knows. They always have
a bug up their ass. Ignore them.

76
00:10:41,017 --> 00:10:43,747
So what heinous misfortune
brings you here?

77
00:10:43,920 --> 00:10:47,583
A month in hell with my dad and his wife.
He's with the EPA.

78
00:10:47,757 --> 00:10:50,692
EPA, cool! Hippies saving the planet.

79
00:10:52,529 --> 00:10:54,019
Look at those goons.

80
00:10:54,164 --> 00:10:57,531
They actually volunteered for this crap.
Can you believe it?

81
00:10:58,535 --> 00:11:00,526
What are you doing here?

82
00:11:00,937 --> 00:11:02,029
Not much.

83
00:11:02,172 --> 00:11:03,935
My dad runs the place.

84
00:11:04,340 --> 00:11:05,773
He does?

85
00:11:10,613 --> 00:11:12,672
Mom? There's somebody here.

86
00:11:45,381 --> 00:11:46,780
Look at this shit.

87
00:11:46,849 --> 00:11:48,942
This is why my dad's an insomniac.

88
00:11:49,252 --> 00:11:52,278
He's afraid she'll burn the house down
in her sleep.

89
00:11:54,657 --> 00:11:57,217
Mom, this is Marti. Marti, my mom.

90
00:12:00,763 --> 00:12:02,492
Vodka. Want some?

91
00:12:04,334 --> 00:12:08,395
Mom's an alcoholic.
The experts say that means I'll be one too.

92
00:12:10,907 --> 00:12:12,841
Let's go. Come on.

93
00:12:13,109 --> 00:12:15,339
Nice to meet you, Mrs. Platt.

94
00:12:47,777 --> 00:12:50,610
And I don't know what's wrong
with the kids.

95
00:12:50,680 --> 00:12:54,673
They treat me like I'm some stranger
rather than their father.

96
00:13:00,223 --> 00:13:01,850
Why are you here?

97
00:13:02,258 --> 00:13:03,486
What do you want?

98
00:13:26,182 --> 00:13:28,810
You're young, but you're old.

99
00:13:29,652 --> 00:13:32,985
Steve, you're going to get a mucho kiss.

100
00:13:36,326 --> 00:13:38,419
Time for your mucho.

101
00:13:42,498 --> 00:13:45,194
Carol doesn't like mucho kisses.

102
00:13:50,940 --> 00:13:52,874
- Hi, honey.
- Did we wake you?

103
00:13:52,942 --> 00:13:54,273
- Sorry.
- What's wrong?

104
00:13:54,344 --> 00:13:55,777
I had a nightmare.

105
00:13:55,945 --> 00:13:59,005
Come here. I'll give you a kiss
and a big hug.

106
00:13:59,415 --> 00:14:01,212
A bad dream can't hurt you.

107
00:14:01,284 --> 00:14:03,718
Everybody has bad dreams, honey.

108
00:14:04,020 --> 00:14:05,214
It's okay.

109
00:14:05,355 --> 00:14:08,518
It's okay. Come on,
I'll take you back to bed.

110
00:14:11,027 --> 00:14:12,722
What the hell was that?

111
00:14:39,055 --> 00:14:41,080
Have you ever been in the military?

112
