It seems to me...

115
00:14:59,275 --> 00:15:02,767
...that it'd be a lot more dangerous
to move this stuff around...

116
00:15:02,912 --> 00:15:05,278
...than to leave it where it is.

117
00:15:05,348 --> 00:15:09,284
If these chemicals are safely stored,
you have nothing to worry about.

118
00:15:09,852 --> 00:15:12,082
I have nothing to worry about?

119
00:15:12,288 --> 00:15:13,585
Explain that.

120
00:15:21,097 --> 00:15:22,621
Come in here, Captain.

121
00:15:26,169 --> 00:15:27,136
Yes, sir.

122
00:15:27,203 --> 00:15:31,299
Escort Dr. Malone around the base.
Show him what he needs to see.

123
00:15:31,441 --> 00:15:33,875
Let him take samples and run tests.

124
00:15:34,043 --> 00:15:37,274
Then do whatever you have to
to expedite his departure.

125
00:16:00,336 --> 00:16:01,564
Mr. Malone?

126
00:16:05,842 --> 00:16:07,400
Good afternoon, sir.

127
00:16:07,577 --> 00:16:09,010
- Can I help you?
- Yeah.

128
00:16:09,078 --> 00:16:12,479
Can you give us some space?
I want to talk to him.

129
00:16:17,954 --> 00:16:20,320
I'm Major Collins,
head of the base medical corps.

130
00:16:20,423 --> 00:16:21,583
Hold on.

131
00:16:24,861 --> 00:16:26,795
I wanted to meet you...

132
00:16:26,863 --> 00:16:30,162
...and extend my cooperation
to you personally.

133
00:16:30,533 --> 00:16:31,830
Thank you.

134
00:16:34,637 --> 00:16:38,971
I'm very interested in the effects exposure
to these chemicals can have on people.

135
00:16:39,141 --> 00:16:40,369
Effects?

136
00:16:41,544 --> 00:16:45,605
You got a lot of chemicals on this base.
They're all pretty toxic.

137
00:16:45,781 --> 00:16:48,682
Effects? Physically,
they could be devastating.

138
00:16:48,784 --> 00:16:52,117
Not physically. I'm referring
to psychological effects.

139
00:16:52,288 --> 00:16:53,949
I'm not following you.

140
00:16:54,123 --> 00:16:57,115
Can they affect brain patterns?

141
00:16:57,527 --> 00:17:00,792
Can they interfere with
chemo-neurological processes?

142
00:17:00,963 --> 00:17:03,329
Can they foster psychoses, paranoias...

143
00:17:03,699 --> 00:17:05,291
...narcophobias?

144
00:17:05,701 --> 00:17:08,534
I'm a chemist, not a psychiatrist.

145
00:17:08,704 --> 00:17:09,932
I don't know.

146
00:17:10,306 --> 00:17:11,534
Simply...

147
00:17:12,375 --> 00:17:14,969
...can they alter one's view of reality?

148
00:17:15,811 --> 00:17:17,210
Let me be frank.

149
00:17:18,147 --> 00:17:20,411
I'm seeing people at the infirmary...

150
00:17:20,650 --> 00:17:22,345
...who are exhibiting...

151
00:17:22,485 --> 00:17:25,477
...extreme delusional fixations.

152
00:17:26,556 --> 00:17:27,716
People...

153
00:17:28,224 --> 00:17:30,419
...afraid to sleep.

154
00:17:30,993 --> 00:17:32,927
People afraid to...

155
00:17:34,163 --> 00:17:36,996
...deal with family members.
Afraid of them.

156
00:17:37,733 --> 00:17:38,995
Exhibiting...

157
00:17:39,569 --> 00:17:41,799
...paranoia about others...

158
00:17:41,871 --> 00:17:44,203
...about other people's identities.

159
00:17:45,241 --> 00:17:47,072
People afraid of themselves.

160
00:17:50,446 --> 00:17:53,847
Suddenly, I got a camp full
of very displaced people.

161
00:17:54,951 --> 00:17:58,682
I don't know what you're seeing,
but it's not the PCBs.

162
00:17:58,854 --> 00:18:01,846
That phenomenon is not
part of the symptomology.

163
00:18:04,360 --> 00:18:06,954
Keep me up to date on your research.

164
00:18:08,764 --> 00:18:10,857
I'm worried about these... people.

165
00:18:17,540 --> 00:18:19,371
Better take a vacation, Doc.

166
00:18:30,553 --> 00:18:32,885
We have equipment for Dr. Malone.

167
00:18:35,391 --> 00:18:36,551
Come in.

168
00:19:30,846 --> 00:19:32,507
What are you doing in there?

169
00:19:32,581 --> 00:19:34,242
Delivering the boxes.

170
00:19:34,550 --> 00:19:35,949
Are you through?

171
00:19:44,627 --> 00:19:45,855
Good.

172
00:19:48,564 --> 00:19:50,122
Very good.

173
00:19:53,969 --> 00:19:55,163
Good work.

174
00:19:57,206 --> 00:19:58,901
Very good work.

175
00:20:07,383 --> 00:20:08,816
Very good.

176
00:20:11,721 --> 00:20:13,552
Okay, all done?

177
00:20:15,791 --> 00:20:18,624
Everyone hold your picture up.

178
00:20:21,330 --> 00:20:22,524
Very good.

179
00:20:25,601 --> 00:20:26,898
Good.

180
00:20:27,603 --> 00:20:28,968
Very good.

